f I am beating a dead horse unwittingly.  I was curious, given the second flooir of hate requires that the first floor be cleared, and given that most raids take an average (I am guessing here) of 8-10 hours to clear floor one from port up to the last revenant (Please don't mock me too much if my raids are slow<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  is there any consensus as to how floor two is covered?  Would it be rude to arrange for a group to tag team floor two after a scheduled raid clears floor one if both Raid Leaders work out the arrangements and the floors are repoped by the time the next crew comes up?<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts as I have enjoyed hunting floor two myself, but have had diffculties keeping my raids momentum after clearing all of floor one.  Perhaps it is simply my deficiencies as a raid Leader, though in truth Evoluxa raids are tolerably fast and reasonably well excuted.<br>
<br>
Eoral Solis<br>
Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukraghack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraghack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 722<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/15/01 1:29:21 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hate 2nd Floor Question</span><hr size=1> <br>
We've found that clearing the first floor isn't really necessary before moving to the second floor.  Generally we will clear from the portal house to Maestro, kill him, then go upstairs.  If there are boss mobs up on the first floor we try to kill those also.  If it's a weekend raid we would probably clear the whole first floor before moving up.<br>
<br>
Our times are a little different from yours though.  For us to port up and clear to Maestro would take about 2 hours.  To clear the entire first floor would be between 3 and 4 hours.  Once we're on the second floor it takes around 2 hours to get to and kill Inny unless something bad happens.<br>
<br>
If you are willing to share your raid with someone else it shouldn't be a problem to have a raid on the first floor and the second floor at the same time.  WIth serverfilter the lag has been very low in hate lately.  It can still get bad, but not so bad that the whole raid goes linkdead like it used to be.<br>
